{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "At the Center for Computational Thinking & Design, we are concerned with developing critical AI literacy in K-12 education using a design based research approach and participatory design to work closely with teachers during the entire research process.",
    "We present research investigating how to design tools for teaching about the underlying models of natural language processing and about the training of large language models (LLMs) in high schools, while exploring what creative expressions students engage in when interacting with these tools, see Figure 3 (Musaeus et al., 2023).",
    "Also, we are studying how students' and teachers' creative interactions with AI systems change after participating in teaching interventions in which these tools are applied, and if knowledge is retained.",
    "Finally, we are investigating if and how knowledge and interactions transfer to other contexts outside formal education, leading to computational competent, critical, and creative students.",
    "Research such as described above will hopefully give an indication of the opportunities and challenges associated with AI and ML applications in education, e.g."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "We present research investigating how to design tools for teaching about the underlying models of natural language processing and about the training of large language models (LLMs) in high schools, while exploring what creative expressions students engage in when interacting with these tools, see Figure 3 (Musaeus et al., 2023)."
  ]
